01-t.webp" type="image/webp"><source srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71756/aImg/52589/66101-ts-april-digest-header-beyond-the-bench-ac-01-t.png" type="image/png"><img src="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71756/aImg/52589/66101-ts-april-digest-header-beyond-the-bench-ac-01-t.png" alt="A scientist is at his desk with two computer monitors in front of him." title="A scientist is at his desk with two computer monitors in front of him." loading="lazy"></picture></a></div><div class="articleTabText flex flex-col"><a href="/behind-the-scenes-of-the-publication-process-71756" target="_self"><div class="h3 max-2-lines l-h-3">Behind the Scenes of the Publication Process</div><div class="h3 max-4-lines l-h-3">Behind the Scenes of the Publication Process</div></a></div></div><div class="articleTab"><div class="articleTabImg"><a href="/multicellular-bacteria-evolve-defenses-that-resemble-the-immune-system-71807" target="_self"><picture><source srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71807/aImg/52797/multicellular-bacteria-evolve-defenses-that-resemble-the-immune-system-t.webp" type="image/webp"><source srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71807/aImg/52797/multicellular-bacteria-evolve-defenses-that-resemble-the-immune-system-t.png" type="image/png"><img src="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71807/aImg/52797/multicellular-bacteria-evolve-defenses-that-resemble-the-immune-system-t.png" alt="A microscopic image of a pink berry bacterial aggregate." title="A microscopic image of a pink berry bacterial aggregate." loading="lazy"></picture></a></div><div class="articleTabText flex flex-col"><a href="/multicellular-bacteria-evolve-defenses-that-resemble-the-immune-system-71807" target="_self"><div class="h3 max-2-lines l-h-3">Multicellular Bacteria Evolve Defenses that Resemble the Immune System</div><div class="h3 max-4-lines l-h-3">Multicellular Bacteria Evolve Defenses that Resemble the Immune System</div></a></div></div><div class="articleTab"><div class="articleTabImg"><a href="/microbial-clocks-for-corpses-71797" target="_self"><picture><source srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71797/aImg/52760/67875-800-x-560-4-t.webp" type="image/webp"><source srcset="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71797/aImg/52760/67875-800-x-560-4-t.jpg" type="image/jpeg"><img src="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/assets/articleNo/71797/aImg/52760/67875-800-x-560-4-t.jpg" alt="Collection of microbes superimposed over a human illustration." title="Collection of microbes superimposed over a human illustration." loading="lazy"></picture></a></div><div class="articleTabText flex flex-col"><a href="/microbial-clocks-for-corpses-71797" target="_self"><div class="h3 max-2-lines l-h-3">Microbial Clocks for Corpses</div><div class="h3 max-4-lines l-h-3">Microbial Clocks for Corpses</div></a></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="relatedCSD" data-tags="{&quot;categoryTags&quot;:[1622],&quot;normalTags&quot;:[6307,2134,8279,7630,6766,6743,1979,5712,4040,4694,4077,6381]}" data-excludedarticles="66244,71827,71756,71807,71797" data-articleno="66244"></div><div class="mobile-ad-marker"></div><div id="Trending"></div><div class="mobile-ad-marker"></div><div class="mobile-ad-marker"></div><div id="Media"></div></div><div id="CurrentIssue"></div><section class="advertisement" data-zone="TS_WEB_ROS_LEADERBOARD_BOTTOM_728X90" id="ts-web-ros-leaderboard-bottom-728x90"></section><small class="adverts">ADVERTISEMENT</small><div id="Sponsored"></div><div id="Marketplace"></div><footer id="MainFooter"><div class="main-container"><header><div class="h1">Stay Connected with</div><img class="logo" src="https://cdn.the-scientist.com/static/7.7.8/assets/TSNewsAlerts.png" alt="TS News Alerts Logo" loading="lazy"></header><div id="NewsletterSignUp"><script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/v2.js" defer></script><script>setTimeout(function(){
